  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>skin-to-skin contact + sucrose</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Experimental</arm_group_type>
    <description>the infants get 2 eye examinations within 1 week in randomized order, one in skin-to-skin position with a parent (intervention group) and one in the incubator (standard care). Sucrose (0.2 ml) lingual will be given for pain relief according to standard care two minutes before either eye examination.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>incubator + sucrose</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>the infants get 2 eye examinations within 1 week in randomized order, one in the incubator (standard care) and one in skin-to-skin position with a parent (intervention group). Sucrose (0.2 ml) lingual will be given for pain relief according to standard care two minutes before either eye examination</description>
